sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61206
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transposable element with spectinomycin resistance marker and (if it worked better) a promoterless gentimicin marker that can be used to select for transposons that have fallen inside a transcribed region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Kittleson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61202
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Construction intermediate for a transposon selectable for insertion into a transcribed region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Kittleson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61205
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Construction intermediate for a transposon with a spectinomycin selection marker inside of the transposed region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Kittleson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Plasmid seems to be stable in DH10B, but not TG1.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J23012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: it is a Spec resistant biobrick
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Will Bosworth
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PCR JL1/JL2 on wt. pSPlam (917bp, EcoRI/SpeI, Neb2) Paste into pSB1A2-I13521 (EcoRI/SpeI, Neb2, Large 2062)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rbsGenR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Gentamicin resistance gene including a medium/weak ribosome binding site, but NO promoter. Intended for use in transposons, to select for elements that fall inside of a transcribed region. The RBS does not appear to be strong enough for this purpose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Kittleson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Tn5F
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: DNA substrate for Tn5 transposase. Flanking a sequence with J61021 on the 5' end and J61022 on the 3' end makes it a functional transposon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson
